1) install shit
	git (to fetch the source)
	python2
	python-pip
	apache2
	memcached
	mysql-server
	python-mysqldb
	libapache2-mod-wsgi
	-> pip :
		django
		suds
		python-memcached
		django-nose
		simplejson

2) get source
	git clone https://github.com/nire/Charlie

3) configure all of this shit
	enable module wsgi in apache conf
	edit Charlie/charlie/tmg.wsgi
	include Charlie/apache_conf/charlie in apache conf
	in this file, edit the lines :
		ServerAdmin
		Aliases
		DocumentRoot
		Directories
		WSGIScriptAlias
	create user on mysql with full rights on a database named "charlie" :
		CREATE USER 'myuser'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'mypassword';
		CREATE DATABASE mydatabase;
		GRANT ALL ON mydatabase.* TO 'myuser'@'localhost';
	edit Charlie/charlie/settings.py
		see django doc
	restart all services : mysql, apache, memcached
